The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 10 January is 163,998 (18,901.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 January, there were 12,444 new confirmed cases (1,434.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 December, there were 11,225 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 11% (1,219 extra cases).
